</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B044001D6DAA23AB6176A0706CE652BB" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="0FBF414BA5424F356F611D6A1963806D" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00313EBA761EF268C1C5DE7AE86AACD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Holotype: ♂, CHINA: Hainan Province, Jianfeng ridge, Nanwang forest, 22.IV.2014, Wei-cheng Yang leg.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="93EB5EC6FF56265DBBC36B2905435A6A" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="FE00202078463CCB7F2F73ACCD7C0617" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="23127B55779618ED745A963D3D120EF1" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">The new species can be distinguished by the shape of the aedeagus with abruptly angled shaft sub-basally and with a long single crest-like dorsomedial flange.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3661F43446C0D293A2A56CD5F39C88C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FC211C266B1E744E92D8C4511B7AEA3C" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A138659CD7FE5C5B43E1DF3BC0AC795" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">The new species name is an adjective derived from the Latin words multi and punctatum referring to the many fine dark spots on the body.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
